is merely the tool, and the person kills.

276
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:47,870
That makes sense does it not?

277
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,390
The sword is a weapon.

278
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:54,070
Swordsmanship is learning how to kill.

279
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:58,740
No matter how much you sugar coat it,
that is the truth.

280
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:02,590
I believe that is the truth.

281
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:04,750
But what Kaoru-dono is saying,

282
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:08,150
I kind of like that idea better.

283
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:53,110
Get him!

284
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:48,620
The style of Hitokiri Battousai
is Hiten Mitsurugi Ryu.

285
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:57,190
It is a style meant to fight many.

286
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:03,230
As long as it's this sword.

287
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,750
None of you will die.

288
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:14,420
You!

289
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:49,430
You're...

290
00:39:58,120 --> 00:39:59,340
Kaoru-chan!

291
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,910
Did something happen?!

292
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:05,390
They're dead!

293
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:08,830
Wait a minute!

294
00:40:08,960 --> 00:40:10,270
What happened... was that?

295
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,380
Is he the killer?!

296
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:12,430
You're mistaken!

297
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:14,590
These people were vandals!

298
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:15,940
But everything's fine.

299
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:18,750
No one was killed. Just unconscious.

300
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:20,590
Over here!

301
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:23,790
What happened here?!

302
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,830
Don't you guys know it is
forbidden to wear swords!

303
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,150
Arrest them!

304
00:40:40,360 --> 00:40:41,470
What happened?

305
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:47,790
Don't blame them.

306
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:52,270
I am a wanderer and I happened to pass by.

307
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:56,470
This dojo has nothing
to do with any of this.

308
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:00,460
Let's go!

309
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:04,500
Hold it!

310
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:07,630
Rurouni-san...

311
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:11,350
What is it?

312
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:16,820
Tell me your name.

313
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:17,670
Ororo!

314
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:18,980
Wait a minute!

315
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:25,350
Himura Kenshin.

316
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:26,790
Out of the way!

317
00:41:28,680 --> 00:41:29,870
Kenshin?

318
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:34,350
Heart of Sword?

319
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:44,750
Shut the fuck up!

320
00:41:51,440 --> 00:41:52,550
A newbie!

321
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:58,020
Walk quickly!

322
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:54,740
Open!

323
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:14,950
The man with the cross-shaped scar.

324
00:43:20,120 --> 00:43:21,790
It was you.

325
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,470
It's been awhile.

326
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:28,590
Hitokiri Battousai.

327
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:34,850
It's been 10 years since the
battle at Toba Fushimi.

328
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:41,460
What's your story?

329
00:43:44,440 --> 00:43:45,100
Retired?

330
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:20,040
Hitokiri Battousai...?

331
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:40,870
It's been a long time,
where have you been?

332
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:43,070
Yamagata-san!

333
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:50,870
I suppose your disappearance
in the last decade

334
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:56,550
is testament to your devotion
to "never killing again."

335
00:44:59,080 --> 00:45:00,060
What?

336
00:45:02,920 --> 00:45:03,950
This man?

337
00:45:04,960 --> 00:45:09,070
That was a different era.

338
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:13,750
I wanted a better country.

339
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:22,910
Now, it is Fujita Goro's job to protect.

340
00:45:25,880 --> 00:45:27,590
What do you want with me?

341
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:30,430
These things are purchased openly.

342
00:45:34,280 --> 00:45:35,750
Known as "Spider's Web"

343
00:45:36,080 --> 00:45:40,270
Looks ordinary, but its contents
are completely different.

344
00:45:41,600 --> 00:45:43,590
We've come across them a few times now.

345
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:46,950
Opium will destroy a nation.

346
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:51,790
Even the Kano Dynasty was
unable to stop opium.

347
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:57,070
Some of the land became
colonies of England.

348
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:00,270
I am only a wanderer.

349
00:46:01,080 --> 00:46:02,750
Why're you telling me this?

350
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:05,150
If they can make this,

351
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:08,790
no doubt they are planning
something bigger.

352
00:46:21,160 --> 00:46:23,150
Lend me your strength.

353
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:27,470
In return, you will have a
key position in the Army.

354
00:46:32,320 --> 00:46:35,639
Use the strength in these arms once more.

355
00:46:35,640 --> 00:46:38,930
I have no intention of
becoming "hitokiri" again.

356
00:46:47,120 --> 00:46:48,990
"Hitokiri" huh?

357
00:46:50,960 --> 00:46:54,710
That's it? This is for the Restoration!

358
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:57,720
Have you become a fool?

359
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:02,230
What is this joke of a katana?

360
00:47:06,720 --> 00:47:09,510
How does one protect
people without killing?

361
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,870
With this sword...

362
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:17,830
I'm able to protect those around me.

363
00:47:17,920 --> 00:47:19,190
Show me.

364
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:26,390
Because those words are just words
unless you can protect yourself.

365
00:47:44,080 --> 00:47:45,659
I won't draw my sword.

366
00:47:45,660 --> 00:47:46,700
Screw you!

367
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:25,590
Reverse your sword,

368
00:48:26,080 --> 00:48:29,070
or I will make you suffer.

369
00:48:35,670 --> 00:48:37,230
It was like this...

370
00:48:41,010 --> 00:48:42,800
Do you remember those days?

371
00:48:46,960 --> 00:48:49,150
That was me in the past,

372
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:52,110
I don't kill anymore.

373
00:48:59,960 --> 00:49:01,150
Forget it!

374
00:49:27,160 --> 00:49:28,710
I'm sorry.

375
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:32,830
It's okay.

376
00:49:38,840 --> 00:49:40,150
Let him go.

377
00:49:59,360 --> 00:50:01,350
Hey Kaoru?

378
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:34,990
Kaoru!

379
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:35,870
Oh!

380
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:42,590
Hey! Are you okay?!

381
00:50:44,120 --> 00:50:45,230
Please help!

382
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:46,590
I'm being chased!

383
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:50,060
Please...

384
00:51:00,320 --> 00:51:01,300
Kaoru-dono...

385
00:51:21,480 --> 00:51:23,510
You have nowhere to go, right?

386
00:51:33,520 --> 00:51:34,870
Come with me.

387
00:51:38,440 --> 00:51:40,350
Because you helped me.

388
00:51:45,280 --> 00:51:47,070
I understand.

389
00:51:47,840 --> 00:51:49,229
But I'm the "hitokiri"...

390
00:51:49,230 --> 00:51:50,950
I don't know who that is.

391
00:51:57,480 --> 00:51:59,270
The person I met,

392
00:51:59,920 --> 00:52:02,110
was a wanderer named Kenshin.

393
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:07,590
Everyone has a past they wish to erase.

394
00:52:10,840 --> 00:52:11,710
Right?

395
00:52:15,240 --> 00:52:16,110
Here.

396
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:19,270
Take it!

397
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:25,270
Let's go!

398
00:52:32,520 --> 00:52:33,550
Hurry!

399
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:36,630
Let's go!

400
00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:49,230
Come inside.

401
00:52:50,080 --> 00:52:51,910
Excuse me.

402
00:52:56,640 --> 00:52:57,270
Yahiko

403
00:53:00,440 --> 00:53:03,910
Myojin Yahiko, sometimes
I teach him fencing.

404
00:53:04,760 --> 00:53:06,070
And kind of stays here.

405
00:53:06,840 --> 00:53:10,510
Only because you have no other students.

406
00:53:10,680 --> 00:53:13,110
He has a bad mouth. But
he has a good heart.

407
00:53:13,280 --> 00:53:15,430
Shut up! I'm going to be strong!

408
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:16,950
I know I know.

409
00:53:17,120 --> 00:53:19,390
Kenshin will be staying
with us from today.

410
00:53:20,080 --> 00:53:22,110
Well, I'm the sempai then!

411
00:53:24,320 --> 00:53:26,110
Nice to meet you.

412
00:53:29,360 --> 00:53:33,030
Hey! Introduce me too!

413
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:39,660
Who are you?!

414
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:42,590
She was soaking wet so
I let her take a bath.

415
00:53:42,720 --> 00:53:44,329
Without asking me?!

416
00:53:44,330 --> 00:53:46,990
Hey, who's the gentlemen over there?

417
00:53:51,320 --> 00:53:52,350
Wait! Wait-!

418
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:55,150
A wanderer, Kenshin.

419
00:53:58,040 --> 00:54:00,990
Oh you!

420
00:54:02,040 --> 00:54:03,250
I heard it from this child

421
00:54:05,080 --> 00:54:07,790
Nice to meet you, I am Takani Megumi.

422
00:54:09,440 --> 00:54:10,830
Nice to meet you.

423
00:54:34,520 --> 00:54:36,430
I brought you a change of clothes.

424
00:54:37,160 --> 00:54:38,350
You didn't have to.

425
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,230
These were my fathers,

426
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:46,870
they are all I have left from when I
was a child, but they should fit.

427
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:48,780
Wait...

428
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:52,350
Is the color too much?

429
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:56,710
No... It's fine.

430
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:50,510
"A sword that protects."

431
00:55:59,640 --> 00:56:01,470
Welcome!

432
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:07,390
By the way...

433
00:56:08,480 --> 00:56:11,070
Why are you here?

434
00:56:11,600 --> 00:56:15,870
Oh, she seems to be bothered by my words.

435
00:56:17,520 --> 00:56:19,670
There's not a lot of people
in this area, right?

436
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:22,310
Where's your home? Where are you from?

437
00:56:22,480 --> 00:56:23,460
Secret!

438
00:56:23,600 --> 00:56:25,710
"Mysterious Beauty" sounds nice, right?

439
00:56:25,840 --> 00:56:27,350
Anyway.

440
00:56:30,120 --> 00:56:30,910
Here you go.

441
00:56:31,120 --> 00:56:33,110
Oh, thanks.

442
00:56:36,720 --> 00:56:40,630
I want to thank you for helping me.
Eat as much as you want.

443
00:56:42,800 --> 00:56:43,990
Okay.

444
00:56:49,160 --> 00:56:49,830
Delicious.

445
00:56:50,720 --> 00:56:51,390
Isn't it?

446
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:52,790
Hot! Hot!

447
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:54,990
Eat carefully!

448
00:56:55,200 --> 00:56:56,340
I know!

449
00:56:56,800 --> 00:56:57,860
Kaoru-chan

450
00:56:58,840 --> 00:57:01,400
Things are tough at the dojo, huh?

451
00:57:01,560 --> 00:57:02,540
Tae-san...

452
00:57:03,560 --> 00:57:05,270
Let me know if we can help.

453
00:57:05,720 --> 00:57:06,830
Everyone around here

454
00:57:06,920 --> 00:57:09,590
will help you no matter what happens.

455
00:57:09,920 --> 00:57:11,670
Welcome!

456
00:57:13,520 --> 00:57:15,270
Welcome!

457
00:57:18,200 --> 00:57:20,230
Takeda Kanryu!

458
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:22,780
He's the wealthy merchant who
owns a mansion at the edge of town.

459
00:57:24,560 --> 00:57:25,470
Where is the kitchen?

460
00:57:25,960 --> 00:57:26,910
Over there

461
00:57:35,880 --> 00:57:36,910
Kanryu-sama!

462
00:57:42,880 --> 00:57:44,870
Please excuse me for
interrupting your meal.

463
00:57:46,630 --> 00:57:52,670
Aren't you the person who beat
up the 10 thugs at a nearby dojo?

464
00:57:56,440 --> 00:57:59,910
I am a businessman.

465
00:58:03,560 --> 00:58:04,430
Hey.

466
00:58:06,360 --> 00:58:08,140
We'll be straightforward.

467
00:58:09,560 --> 00:58:12,270
We want to hire you with this money

468
00:58:12,560 --> 00:58:17,470
We can hire 10 people with that.
That's 10 times the amount for one.

469
00:58:17,600 --> 00:58:20,830
What do you think? Want
to be our body guard?

470
00:58:22,240 --> 00:58:24,390
I must refuse.

471
00:58:33,440 --> 00:58:34,990
Is this not enough?

472
00:58:38,920 --> 00:58:40,310
I see.

473
00:58:40,440 --> 00:58:43,150
You're "the samurai who hasn't eaten,
yet picks his teeth"

474
00:58:43,280 --> 00:58:45,270
That's all fine!

475
00:58:46,760 --> 00:58:51,350
But in the Meiji Era,
money is everything!

476
00:58:51,480 --> 00:58:55,310
Unfortunately I don't value such pride.

477
00:58:55,440 --> 00:58:56,870
Unlike this man here.

478
00:58:56,960 --> 00:58:59,150
I do not take such valuables so lightly,

479
00:58:59,280 --> 00:59:00,790
that I can throw it away!

480
00:59:00,880 --> 00:59:03,230
All it takes is one walk
down the red-light district,

481
00:59:03,360 --> 00:59:06,430
and you could lose your wife
or even your daughters!

482
00:59:06,640 --> 00:59:11,270
I am merely trying to free this world
of samurai and catch all bandits!

483
00:59:14,360 --> 00:59:17,470
That life may be fine for samurai.

484
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:21,670
To have fun,

485
00:59:22,000 --> 00:59:23,310
and live,

486
00:59:24,640 --> 00:59:25,780
remember this.

487
00:59:32,320 --> 00:59:33,750
You're being very rude.

488
00:59:48,800 --> 00:59:51,990
You would throw away my money?!

489
00:59:54,040 --> 00:59:55,910
Then give me the money.

490
00:59:56,040 --> 00:59:57,350
Sanosuke-san?

491
00:59:57,440 --> 00:59:58,710
Wa-Wait!

492
01:00:04,680 --> 01:00:06,470
You can hire me.

493
01:00:07,560 --> 01:00:08,700
What are you?

494
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:13,830
Sagara Sanosuke of the Brawlers.

495
01:00:14,040 --> 01:00:16,870
Fishing for money straight out of jail?

496
01:00:17,080 --> 01:00:19,460
Are you worth this much money?

497
01:00:20,640 --> 01:00:22,030
Are those arms?

498
01:00:23,720 --> 01:00:27,500
I'll give it a shot,
against the legendary "hitokiri."

499
01:00:28,200 --> 01:00:29,830
Himura Battousai-san

500
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:31,390
Eh?!

501
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:43,710
How about a fight so they can hire me?

502
01:00:43,880 --> 01:00:46,510
This is not the place.

503
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:49,540
Meet me outside.

504
01:00:52,800 --> 01:00:54,670
Oh! I've been waiting for this!

505
01:00:55,080 --> 01:00:56,118
Come out and watch everyone!

506
01:00:56,119 --> 01:00:56,210
They are going to fight!
Come out and watch everyone!

507
01:00:56,211 --> 01:00:57,910
They are going to fight!

508
01:00:59,920 --> 01:01:00,950
This guy here,

509
01:01:01,960 --> 01:01:05,470
is a horse killing sword called Zanbato.

510
01:01:05,880 --> 01:01:08,440
It's an antique from the Onin Wars.

511
01:01:14,560 --> 01:01:18,790
It doesn't look like you share my tastes.

512
01:01:18,920 --> 01:01:19,790
However...

513
01:01:25,760 --> 01:01:28,590
It can still crush you.

514
01:01:40,440 --> 01:01:41,230
Get over here!

515
01:01:50,160 --> 01:01:51,630
Himura Battousai!

516
01:01:53,280 --> 01:01:54,870
Assassin for the Ishin Shishi Faction,

517
01:01:55,640 --> 01:01:59,260
A killer from the age of 14 to 19.

518
01:02:03,800 --> 01:02:07,390
I've been waiting for this for 10 years!

519
01:02:22,160 --> 01:02:23,190
That's good!

520
01:02:23,840 --> 01:02:24,750
You're in!

521
01:02:25,160 --> 01:02:27,460
Out of the way! Move!

522
01:02:38,600 --> 01:02:40,670
I will not draw my sword.

523
01:02:44,040 --> 01:02:47,150
You'll need your sword to fight me!

524
01:02:49,360 --> 01:02:51,660
You will not touch me
with that huge sword.

525
01:02:51,800 --> 01:02:52,750
Why is that?!

526
01:02:57,880 --> 01:03:00,150
There is no reason to adjust the sword.

527
01:03:09,400 --> 01:03:11,070
That man...

528
01:03:12,160 --> 01:03:14,430
You would fight for a man like him?

529
01:03:21,080 --> 01:03:24,390
Kanryu: What is it?! What's going on!

530
01:03:25,400 --> 01:03:27,590
What's happening over there?!

531
01:03:28,560 --> 01:03:30,230
What are you doing, Brawler?

532
01:03:30,560 --> 01:03:32,150
Hurry up and finish him!

533
01:03:33,600 --> 01:03:34,550
Shut up!

534
01:03:34,880 --> 01:03:37,510
You don't tell me how to
fight from where you are!

535
01:03:37,600 --> 01:03:38,630
Is it over?

536
01:03:51,960 --> 01:03:53,180
Oh well.

537
01:03:54,720 --> 01:03:57,230
I'd probably end up back
at the police station.

538
01:03:59,240 --> 01:04:00,910
The trouble is over folks!

539
01:04:01,480 --> 01:04:02,950
Hey everyone back to the store!

540
01:04:03,160 --> 01:04:04,590
The show is over!

541
01:04:07,360 --> 01:04:08,750
It's over, it's over!

542
01:04:09,320 --> 01:04:10,110
I'll be back!

543
01:04:13,280 --> 01:04:14,870
I ran into trouble.

544
01:04:19,080 --> 01:04:20,590
Let's eat.

545
01:04:20,760 --> 01:04:22,870
We should not be wasteful.

546
01:04:23,840 --> 01:04:25,910
He's the real deal.

547
01:04:27,720 --> 01:04:29,710
You have done well

548
01:04:35,640 --> 01:04:40,630
Battousai is not someone
that can be bought.

549
01:04:41,640 --> 01:04:42,860
Your pleasure!

550
01:04:51,760 --> 01:04:53,790
I need blood!

551
01:04:57,720 --> 01:05:00,350
I need more blood!

552
01:05:02,800 --> 01:05:05,100
I still thirst for more!

553
01:05:07,120 --> 01:05:10,820
I thirst for Hitokiri Battousai!

554
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:26,150
The work of the fake battousai again...

555
01:05:27,080 --> 01:05:32,150
He kills people, policemen,
